{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865837532,"sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","part":{"id":"prt_d79da339f001NZcr7iytD31Osx","messageID":"msg_d79da2df6001tu1MzwqN7QYVP1","sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0665dae1a9e84492b6a993d8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.pytest_cache/\nagentcube_sdk.egg-info/\nagentcube/\ndesign.md\npyproject.toml\nspec.md\ntests/\n\n(7 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".pytest_cache/\nagentcube_sdk.egg-info/\nagentcube/\ndesign.md\npyproject.toml\nspec.md\ntests/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk","time":{"start":1775865837528,"end":1775865837531}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865838692,"sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","part":{"id":"prt_d79da38650015pvARomn4PE9R4","messageID":"msg_d79da2df6001tu1MzwqN7QYVP1","sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c1ea319df3c54c5ca1d3d9b1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: The AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) provides a high-level client library for:\n8: \n9: 1. **Code Interpreter Sessions** — Create/manage sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n10: 2. **Agent Runtime Invocation** — Bootstrap sessions and invoke agent workloads through the Router.\n11: \n12: ### 1.2 Layered Architecture\n13: \n14: ```\n15: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n16: │                    Public Client Layer                      │\n17: │  CodeInterpreterClient  │  AgentRuntimeClient               │\n18: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n19: │                  Data Plane Clients                         │\n20: │  CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient  │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient │\n21: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n22: │                  Control Plane Client                       │\n23: │                     ControlPlaneClient                      │\n24: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n25: │                    HTTP Utilities                           │\n26: │  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger     │\n27: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n31: \n32: - **No single Configuration class** — Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across components.\n33: - **Context manager support** — All public clients implement `__enter__`/`__exit__` for resource cleanup.\n34: - **Session header management** — `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) is used consistently for Router requests.\n35: - **Timeout safety** — Execute command adds +2.0s buffer to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`.\n36: \n37: ### 1.4 Package Layout\n38: \n39: ```\n40: sdk-python/\n41: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Package agentcube-sdk, dependencies\n42: ├── agentcube/\n43: │   ├── __init__.py                    — Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n44: │   ├── code_interpreter.py            — CodeInterpreterClient\n45: │   ├── agent_runtime.py               — AgentRuntimeClient\n46: │   ├── exceptions.py                  — Exception classes\n47: │   ├── clients/\n48: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports client classes\n49: │   │   ├── control_plane.py           — ControlPlaneClient\n50: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n51: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n52: │   └── utils/\n53: │       ├── __init__.py                — Empty (module marker)\n54: │       ├── http.py                    — create_session\n55: │       ├── utils.py                   — read_token_from_file\n56: │       └── log.py                     — get_logger\n57: ├── examples/\n58: │   ├── basic_usage.py                 — CodeInterpreterClient usage examples\n59: │   └── agent_runtime_usage.py         — AgentRuntimeClient usage examples\n60: ├── scripts/\n61: │   └── e2e_picod_test.py              — End-to-end test against PicoD\n62: └── tests/\n63:     └── *.py                           — Unit and integration tests\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n67: \n68: ```toml\n69: dependencies = [\n70:     \"requests\",\n71:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n72:     \"cryptography\",\n73: ]\n74: ```\n75: \n76: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n77: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n78: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 2. Data Structures\n83: \n84: ### 2.1 Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n85: \n86: ```python\n87: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n88:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n89:     pass\n90: \n91: class CommandExecutionError(AgentExecutionError):\n92:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n93:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n94:         self.stderr = stderr\n95:         self.command = command\n96:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n97: \n98: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n99:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n100:     pass\n101: \n102: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n103:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n104:     pass\n105: ```\n106: \n107: **Note:** `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules. Callers may rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`.\n108: \n109: ### 2.2 `CodeInterpreterClient` Fields\n110: \n111: | Field | Type | Description |\n112: |-------|------|-------------|\n113: | `name` | `str` | Session name (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n114: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n115: | `ttl` | `int` | Session TTL in seconds (default: `3600`) |\n116: | `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging |\n117: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Logger instance |\n118: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane HTTP client |\n119: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n120: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Active session ID |\n121: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client |\n122: \n123: ### 2.3 `AgentRuntimeClient` Fields\n124: \n125: | Field | Type | Description |\n126: |-------|------|-------------|\n127: | `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name |\n128: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n129: | `timeout` | `int` | Default read timeout (default: `120`) |\n130: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connect timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n131: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Logger instance |\n132: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n133: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Active session ID |\n134: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client |\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## 3. API Contracts\n139: \n140: ### 3.1 Public Exports\n141: \n142: #### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n143: \n144: ```python\n145: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n146: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n147: \n148: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n149: ```\n150: \n151: #### `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n152: \n153: ```python\n154: from .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n155: from .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n156: from .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n157: \n158: __all__ = [\n159:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n160:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n161:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n162: ]\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ### 3.2 `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n166: \n167: ```python\n168: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n169:     def __init__(\n170:         self,\n171:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n172:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n173:         ttl: int = 3600,\n174:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n175:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n176:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n177:         verbose: bool = False,\n178:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n179:     )\n180: \n181:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None\n182:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n183:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n184:     def stop(self) -> None\n185:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n186:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n187:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n188:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n189:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n190:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n191: ```\n192: \n193: #### Configuration Resolution\n194: \n195: | Setting | Source |\n196: |---------|--------|\n197: | `router_url` | Argument or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n198: | `workload_manager_url` | Argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n199: | `auth_token` | Argument or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n200: | `name` | Argument (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n201: | `namespace` | Argument (default: `\"default\"`) |\n202: | `ttl` | Argument (default: `3600`) |\n203: | `session_id` | Argument (optional; if provided, skips session creation) |\n204: \n205: #### Lifecycle\n206: \n207: 1. **Init:** Resolve `router_url` → raise `ValueError` if missing. Create `ControlPlaneClient`. If `session_id` is `None`, call `create_session()`. Call `_init_data_plane()`.\n208: 2. **Data plane init failure:** If `_init_data_plane()` raises after session creation, log warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id = None`, re-raise.\n209: 3. **Context manager exit:** Call `stop()` → close data plane session, delete control plane session (if `session_id` set), close control plane HTTP session.\n210: \n211: ### 3.3 `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n212: \n213: ```python\n214: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n215:     def __init__(\n216:         self,\n217:         agent_name: str,\n218:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n219:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n220:         verbose: bool = False,\n221:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n222:         timeout: int = 120,\n223:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n224:     )\n225: \n226:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n227:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n228:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n229:     def close(self) -> None\n230: ```\n231: \n232: #### Lifecycle\n233: \n234: 1. **Init:** Resolve `router_url`. Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. If `session_id` is `None`, call `bootstrap_session_id()` via `GET` on invocation base URL. Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header; if missing, raise `ValueError`.\n235: 2. **Invoke:** If `session_id` is falsy, raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`.\n236: 3. **Context manager exit:** Call `close()` → close underlying `requests.Session`.\n237: \n238: ### 3.4 `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n239: \n240: ```python\n241: class ControlPlaneClient:\n242:     def __init__(\n243:         self,\n244:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n245:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n246:         timeout: int = 120,\n247:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n248:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n249:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n250:     )\n251: \n252:     def create_session(\n253:         self,\n254:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n255:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n256:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n257:         ttl: int = 3600,\n258:     ) -> str\n259: \n260:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool\n261:     def close(self) -> None\n262: ```\n263: \n264: #### HTTP Endpoints\n265: \n266: | Method | Path | Body / Notes |\n267: |--------|------|--------------|\n268: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON: `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` → returns `data[\"sessionId\"]` |\n269: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success (returns `True`) |\n270: \n271: #### Headers\n272: \n273: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n274: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n275: \n276: #### Timeout\n277: \n278: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n279: \n280: ### 3.5 `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n281: \n282: ```python\n283: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n284:     def __init__(\n285:         self,\n286:         session_id: str,\n287:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n288:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n289:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n290:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n291:         timeout: int = 120,\n292:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n293:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n294:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n295:     )\n296: \n297:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response\n298:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n299:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n300:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n301:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n302:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n303:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n304:     def close(self) -> None\n305: ```\n306: \n307: #### Base URL Resolution\n308: \n309: If `base_url` is not provided:\n310: \n311: ```python\n312: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n313: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n314: ```\n315: \n316: #### HTTP Endpoints (relative to `self.base_url`)\n317: \n318: | Method | Relative Path | Body / Params |\n319: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n320: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n321: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n322: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n323: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n324: | `GET` | `api/files` | Query `path` |\n325: \n326: #### Headers\n327: \n328: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n329: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n330: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n331: \n332: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n333: \n334: #### Timeout Behavior\n335: \n336: `execute_command` adds +2.0s buffer to read timeout to avoid premature `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124.\n337: \n338: ### 3.6 `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n339: \n340: ```python\n341: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n342:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n343: \n344:     def __init__(\n345:         self,\n346:         router_url: str,\n347:         namespace: str,\n348:         agent_name: str,\n349:         timeout: int = 120,\n350:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n351:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n352:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n353:     )\n354: \n355:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str\n356:     def invoke(self, session_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> requests.Response\n357:     def close(self) -> None\n358: ```\n359: \n360: #### Base URL\n361: \n362: ```python\n363: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n364: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n365: ```\n366: \n367: #### HTTP Endpoints\n368: \n369: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n370: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n371: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers | — |\n372: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n373: \n374: #### Timeouts\n375: \n376: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` is method argument or `self.timeout`.\n377: \n378: ### 3.7 Utility Functions\n379: \n380: #### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n381: \n382: ```python\n383: def create_session(\n384:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n385:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n386: ) -> requests.Session:\n387: ```\n388: \n389: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n390: \n391: #### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n392: \n393: ```python\n394: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n395: ```\n396: \n397: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n398: \n399: #### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n400: \n401: ```python\n402: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n403: ```\n404: \n405: ---\n406: \n407: ## 4. Configuration Summary\n408: \n409: | Component | Resolved Settings |\n410: |-----------|-------------------|\n411: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n412: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n413: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n414: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n415: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults as above |\n416: \n417: ---\n418: \n419: ## 5. Error Handling\n420: \n421: ### 5.1 Exception Flow\n422: \n423: ```\n424: AgentCubeError (base)\n425: ├── CommandExecutionError  ← execute_command with exit_code != 0\n426: ├── SessionError           ← session creation/management failures (defined, not raised)\n427: └── DataPlaneError         ← data plane operation failures (defined, not raised)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ### 5.2 Error Scenarios\n431: \n432: | Scenario | Behavior |\n433: |----------|----------|\n434: | Command non-zero exit | Raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` |\n435: | Router URL missing | Raise `ValueError` in `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n436: | Session bootstrap header missing | Raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` |\n437: | Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` |\n438: | Delete session 404 | Return `True` (treated as success) |\n439: | Delete session other failure | Log and return `False` |\n440: | Data plane init failure after session create | Log warning, delete session, set `session_id=None`, re-raise |\n441: \n442: ### 5.3 Timeout Behavior\n443: \n444: | Component | Default Read Timeout | Default Connect Timeout |\n445: |-----------|---------------------|------------------------|\n446: | ControlPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n447: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n448: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n449: | `execute_command` | `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (buffer to avoid ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124) | 5.0s |\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ## 6. Implementation Notes\n454: \n455: ### 6.1 Python Code Execution Path\n456: \n457: When `run_code` is called with `language` in `[\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\"]`:\n458: \n459: 1. Generate timestamped filename: `f\"/tmp/code_{timestamp}.py\"`\n460: 2. Write code content via `write_file`\n461: 3. Execute via `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\", timeout=timeout)`\n462: \n463: ### 6.2 Session Header Consistency\n464: \n465: All Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n466: \n467: - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Set as default session header in `__init__`\n468: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n469: - Multipart uploads: Explicitly set on POST request (no JSON Content-Type)\n470: \n471: ### 6.3 Timeout Buffer Logic\n472: \n473: For `execute_command`:\n474: \n475: ```python\n476: timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout  # default 120\n477: pico_timeout_str = f\"{timeout_value}s\"\n478: read_timeout = timeout_value + 2.0  # buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n479: ```\n480: \n481: ---\n482: \n483: ## 7. Testing Strategy\n484: \n485: ### 7.1 Test Categories\n486: \n487: | Category | Scope |\n488: |----------|-------|\n489: | Unit tests | Individual client methods, mock HTTP responses |\n490: | Integration tests | Control plane + data plane interaction (mocked servers) |\n491: | E2E tests | Real environment with `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n492: \n493: ### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n494: \n495: #### CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle\n496: \n497: | Test Name | Description |\n498: |-----------|-------------|\n499: | `TestCodeInterpreterClient_ContextManagerCleanup` | `__exit__` calls `stop()`, closes sessions |\n500: | `TestDataPlaneInitFailure_RollbackSession` | Data plane init failure rolls back session |\n501: | `TestRouterUrlRequired_MissingEnv` | Missing `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` → `ValueError` |\n502: \n503: #### Command Execution\n504: \n505: | Test Name | Description |\n506: |-----------|-------------|\n507: | `TestExecuteCommand_NonZeroExit` | Non-zero exit raises `CommandExecutionError` |\n508: | `TestRunCode_PythonExecution` | Python code writes timestamped `.py` file and runs `python3` |\n509: | `TestExecuteCommand_TimeoutBuffer` | Timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied correctly |\n510: \n511: #### File Operations\n512: \n513: | Test Name | Description |\n514: |-----------|-------------|\n515: | `TestWriteFile_Base64Content` | `write_file` sends base64 content with mode `0644` |\n516: | `TestUploadFile_MultipartSessionHeader` | `upload_file` sends multipart with session header |\n517: | `TestDownloadFile_StreamResponse` | `download_file` streams response |\n518: | `TestListFiles_QueryPath` | `list_files` queries with path parameter |\n519: \n520: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n521: \n522: | Test Name | Description |\n523: |-----------|-------------|\n524: | `TestAgentRuntimeClient_BootstrapSessionId` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n525: | `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeWithoutSession` | Invoke validates session ID presence |\n526: | `TestAgentRuntimeClient_ContextManagerClosesSession` | Context manager closes HTTP session |\n527: \n528: #### Control Plane\n529: \n530: | Test Name | Description |\n531: |-----------|-------------|\n532: | `TestControlPlaneClient_CreateSession` | Create session returns `sessionId` |\n533: | `TestControlPlaneClient_DeleteSession404` | Delete session handles 404 gracefully |\n534: | `TestControlPlaneClient_AuthTokenFromSAFile` | Auth token resolution from SA file |\n535: \n536: #### Timeout Behavior\n537: \n538: | Test Name | Description |\n539: |-----------|-------------|\n540: | `TestExecuteCommand_DefaultTimeout` | Default timeouts (120s read, 5.0s connect) |\n541: | `TestExecuteCommand_PerCallOverride` | Per-call override for execute_command |\n542: | `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeTimeoutTuple` | AgentRuntimeClient invoke timeout tuple |\n543: \n544: ### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n545: \n546: - Use `unittest.mock` or `pytest-mock` for `requests.Session`\n547: - Mock `create_session` to return controlled `requests.Session` instances\n548: - Use `responses` library or custom adapters for HTTP endpoint mocking\n\n(End of file - total 548 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) provides a high-level client library for:\n\n1. **Code Interpreter Sessions** — Create/manage sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n2. **Agent Runtime Invocation** — Bootstrap sessions and invoke agent workloads through the Router.\n\n### 1.2 Layered Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public Client Layer                      │\n│  CodeInterpreterClient  │  AgentRuntimeClient               │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                  Data Plane Clients                         │\n│  CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient  │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775865838679,"end":1775865838689}}}}
