{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775865862714,"sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","part":{"id":"prt_d79da9a37001yxSuspQX0RlW4a","messageID":"msg_d79da947e001lFSShIqDLjdDhI","sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865984960,"sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","part":{"id":"prt_d79da9e94001GKVx7jiuwjCCkV","messageID":"msg_d79da947e001lFSShIqDLjdDhI","sessionID":"ses_286260488ffeFuSIgt6fy6nM03","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8b5f275bbec743878bc893c9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient` is a high-level Python SDK client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads through the AgentCube Router. It provides:\n\n1. **Session Bootstrap** — Automatically obtain or reuse `session_id` via the Router's invocation endpoint.\n2. **Agent Invocation** — POST JSON payloads to agent runtime endpoints with proper session management.\n3. **Resource Cleanup** — Context manager support for deterministic HTTP session cleanup.\n\n### 1.2 Position in SDK Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public Client Layer                      │\n│              AgentRuntimeClient (this AR)                   │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                  Data Plane Client                          │\n│              AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient                    │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                    HTTP Utilities                           │\n│  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Design Principles\n\n- **No single Configuration class** — Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across components.\n- **Context manager support** — Implements `__enter__`/`__exit__` for resource cleanup.\n- **Session header management** — `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) is used consistently for Router requests.\n- **Timeout safety** — Default read timeout of 120s with connect timeout of 5.0s.\n\n### 1.4 Package Layout\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Package agentcube-sdk, dependencies\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py               — AgentRuntimeClient (this AR)\n│   ├── exceptions.py                  — Exception classes\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports client classes\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                — Empty (module marker)\n│       ├── http.py                    — create_session\n│       ├── utils.py                   — read_token_from_file\n│       └── log.py                     — get_logger\n├── examples/\n│   └── agent_runtime_usage.py         — AgentRuntimeClient usage examples\n└── tests/\n    └── test_agent_runtime.py          — Unit and integration tests\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n```\n\n- `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n- Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n- Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 `AgentRuntimeClient` Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name (required) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default read timeout in seconds (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connect timeout in seconds (default: `5.0`) |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Logger instance |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Active session ID (bootstrapped or provided) |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client |\n\n### 2.2 `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `SESSION_HEADER` | `str` | Class constant: `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default read timeout (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connect timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n| `base_url` | `str` | Computed invocation base URL |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n\n### 2.3 Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n**Note:** `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules. Callers may rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError` (from code interpreter).\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Public Export\n\n#### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n#### `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n### 3.2 `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    )\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n#### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Setting | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| `router_url` | Argument or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| `agent_name` | Argument (required) |\n| `namespace` | Argument (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `session_id` | Argument (optional; if `None`, bootstrapped via `GET`) |\n| `timeout` | Argument (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | Argument (default: `5.0`) |\n\n#### Lifecycle\n\n1. **Init:**\n   - Resolve `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable.\n   - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with resolved parameters.\n   - If `session_id` is `None`, call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` via `GET` on invocation base URL.\n   - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header from response; if missing, raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`.\n   - Store bootstrapped `session_id` on instance.\n\n2. **Invoke:**\n   - Validate `session_id` is truthy; if falsy, raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`.\n   - Call `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)`.\n   - Return parsed JSON response.\n\n3. **Context manager exit:**\n   - Call `close()` → close underlying `requests.Session`.\n\n4. **Close:**\n   - Call `dp_client.close()` to release HTTP connection pool.\n\n### 3.3 `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n#### Base URL Resolution\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers only | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n#### `bootstrap_session_id()`\n\n- Sends `GET` request to `self.base_url`.\n- Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header from response.\n- Returns session ID string.\n- Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` if header is absent.\n\n#### `invoke()`\n\n- Validates `session_id` is provided.\n- Sends `POST` request to `self.base_url` with:\n  - Header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n  - Header: `Content-Type: application/json`\n  - Body: JSON-serialized `payload`\n- Timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` defaults to `self.timeout` (120s).\n- Returns `requests.Response` object.\n\n#### Timeouts\n\n- Default read timeout: `120` seconds.\n- Default connect timeout: `5.0` seconds.\n- Per-call override via `timeout` parameter in `invoke()`.\n- Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, effective_timeout)`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Summary\n\n| Component | Resolved Settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `router_url`+`namespace`+`agent_name` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Exception Flow\n\n```\nValueError                    ← Configuration errors, missing session, missing headers\nrequests.RequestException     ← HTTP failures (connection errors, timeouts)\nrequests.HTTPError            ← Non-2xx responses (if raised)\n```\n\n### 5.2 Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Behavior |\n|----------|----------|\n| Router URL missing | Raise `ValueError` in `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` |\n| Session bootstrap header missing | Raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` |\n| Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` |\n| HTTP timeout | `requests.Timeout` raised by underlying session |\n| Connection failure | `requests.ConnectionError` raised by underlying session |\n\n### 5.3 Timeout Behavior\n\n| Component | Default Read Timeout | Default Connect Timeout |\n|-----------|---------------------|------------------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 120s | 5.0s |\n| `invoke()` per-call | Method argument or `self.timeout` (120s) | 5.0s |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Notes\n\n### 6.1 Session Bootstrap Flow\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient` can operate in two modes:\n\n1. **Pre-provisioned session:** Caller provides `session_id` in constructor.\n2. **Auto-bootstrap:** Client calls `GET` on invocation base URL to obtain `session_id` from response header.\n\nThe bootstrap mechanism allows the Router to manage session lifecycle and provide a valid session ID for subsequent invocations.\n\n### 6.2 Session Header Consistency\n\nAll Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- Set explicitly on each `POST` request in `invoke()`\n\n### 6.3 Timeout Tuple Logic\n\nFor `invoke()`:\n\n```python\neffective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\nrequest_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n```\n\nThis ensures the connect timeout is always applied, while the read timeout can be overridden per-call.\n\n### 6.4 Context Manager Pattern\n\n```python\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\") as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"query\", \"data\": {\"key\": \"value\"}})\n# Session automatically closed on exit\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### 7.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope |\n|----------|-------|\n| Unit tests | Individual client methods, mock HTTP responses |\n| Integration tests | Data plane interaction (mocked servers) |\n| E2E tests | Real environment with Router backend |\n\n### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient Lifecycle\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_BootstrapSessionId` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeWithoutSession` | Invoke validates session ID presence |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_ContextManagerClosesSession` | Context manager closes HTTP session |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_PreProvisionedSession` | Uses provided session_id without bootstrap |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_MissingRouterUrl` | Raises ValueError when router_url missing |\n\n#### Session Bootstrap\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestBootstrapSessionId_Success` | GET returns valid session header |\n| `TestBootstrapSessionId_MissingHeader` | Raises ValueError when header absent |\n| `TestBootstrapSessionId_NetworkError` | Handles connection failures gracefully |\n\n#### Invoke\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestInvoke_Success` | POST returns valid JSON response |\n| `TestInvoke_WithTimeout` | Per-call timeout override applied |\n| `TestInvoke_DefaultTimeout` | Uses instance default timeout (120s) |\n| `TestInvoke_SessionHeader` | Includes x-agentcube-session-id header |\n| `TestInvoke_ContentTypeHeader` | Includes Content-Type: application/json |\n\n#### Timeout Behavior\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeTimeoutTuple` | AgentRuntimeClient invoke timeout tuple |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_DefaultTimeouts` | Default timeouts (120s read, 5.0s connect) |\n\n### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n\n- Use `unittest.mock` or `pytest-mock` for `requests.Session`.\n- Mock `create_session` to return controlled `requests.Session` instances.\n- Use `responses` library or custom adapters for HTTP endpoint mocking.\n- Mock `GET` response with `x-agentcube-session-id` header for bootstrap tests.\n- Mock `POST` response with JSON payload for invoke tests.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Usage Examples\n\n### 8.1 Basic Usage with Context Manager\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"production\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\n        \"action\": \"process\",\n        \"data\": {\"input\": \"hello world\"}\n    })\n    print(response)\n```\n\n### 8.2 Pre-provisioned Session\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n)\n\ntry:\n    response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"query\"})\nfinally:\n    client.close()\n```\n\n### 8.3 Custom Timeout\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    timeout=300,  # 5 minute read timeout\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke(\n        {\"action\": \"long_running_task\"},\n        timeout=600  # Override to 10 minutes for this call\n    )\n```\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775865984892,"end":1775865984956}}}}
